                            target="_blank">step-by-step instructions on how to sign up for a free trial</a>.</li>
                        <li>Watch a <a href="http://video.ch9.ms/ch9/abf4/8b90c323-e8d2-4cef-8259-9fff0010abf4/AtHomeS1_ch9.wmv"
                            target="_blank">small video on Azure Free Trial</a>.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <strong>It's free, you will not be charged.</strong></p>
                    <p>
                        In both cases you will need to use a credit card. The card is used solely to prove
                        you are over 18 and a real human. Windows Azure has a spending cap in place for MSDN
                        and trial accounts that will keep you from spending more than your free allocation
                        of resources, so you credit card WILL NEVER BE CHARGED.</p>
